<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-03-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-03-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-05"><hi rend="italic">March 5,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 101.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 200, of the 9th ultimo, reporting your visit to the President of the
                            Dominican Republic, during which you conveyed to him the congratulations
                            of the President and Government of the United States.</p>
                        <p>Your course is approved, and the Department appreciates the friendly
                            assurances you received from the President.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>